def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    # Retain the original indices for unstacking
    orig_index = list(index.names)
    orig_levels = index.levels
    orig_codes = index.codes

    # Extract the level to be unstacked
    to_unstack_name = index.names[clocs[0]]
    to_unstack_level = index._get_level_number(to_unstack_name)

    # Reset to default index
    data = data.reset_index()

    # Unstack the specified level
    unstacked = data.unstack(level=to_unstack_level, fill_value=fill_value)

    # Restore the original indices
    unstacked.columns = orig_index + [c[1] for c in unstacked.columns]

    # Convert back to a MultiIndex
    unstacked = unstacked.set_index(orig_index)

    return unstacked
